Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on stone block showing figure of elephant, pecked in outline and infilled with pecking, human figure and figure of cow. All figures upright, elephant central and large, with ear lacking infill, facing right. Human figure is tiny in relation, standing to left of elephant and holding elephant’s tail in right hand, other hand raised, facing right. Cow figure intersects with elephant’s left foreleg, is upright and facing left, incised rather than pecked and schematic. Alec Campbell standing on the right. New Kalabsha, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
